menu.name: Biryani
menu.description: Biryani is a classic Indian dish that is beloved for its aromatic flavors, rich spices, and tender meat or vegetables. This hearty rice-based dish is a staple in many parts of India and has become popular worldwide for its unique taste and texture.  The preparation of biryani involves layering cooked rice and a mixture of meat or vegetables with fragrant spices such as saffron, cumin, and cardamom. The dish is then slow-cooked on a low flame, allowing the flavors to blend together and creating a tender and juicy biryani.

menu.name: Veg Pulav
menu.description: Veg pulav is a classic Indian rice dish that is loaded with vegetables and aromatic spices. This dish is perfect for a wholesome and filling meal that is also easy to prepare.  The dish is made by cooking a mix of vegetables such as carrots, beans, peas, and potatoes with aromatic spices like cumin, cardamom, and cinnamon. Once the vegetables are tender, they are combined with long-grain basmati rice and cooked together with water or vegetable stock until the rice is perfectly cooked.  Veg pulav is typically served with a side of raita or a cooling yogurt-based dip to complement the spices in the dish. It can also be enjoyed with a variety of sides such as papadums, pickles, or chutneys.
